<span id="freeTextContainer8246391314990513018">Because I check my goodreads list before I buy books, in this I had misled myself. Sometimes I sit down at the library and read books, start to finish, and this had been one of those. I recall thinking at the time that I did not find the book as interesting as most of the Cadfael books because of the descriptions of battle. I like battle scenes...just not the ones written by this lady who did such a good job on the softer side of things. Anyway, glad I bought it just the same and enjoyed the rat</span>
  <span id="freeText8246391314990513018" style="display:none">Because I check my goodreads list before I buy books, in this I had misled myself. Sometimes I sit down at the library and read books, start to finish, and this had been one of those. I recall thinking at the time that I did not find the book as interesting as most of the Cadfael books because of the descriptions of battle. I like battle scenes...just not the ones written by this lady who did such a good job on the softer side of things. Anyway, glad I bought it just the same and enjoyed the rather healthier dose of consternation over what may or may not be justice and the differences between the English and the Welsh in that determination. Cadfael puts his Welsh to good use in this one.</span>
