        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1514500850" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2121456050039201663">When Sheriff Prescote is taken captive in battle, his deputy, Hugh Beringar, seeks to exchange a young Welsh prisoner for him. The deal is made, and the injured sheriff is brought home, only to fall prey to murder. The resolution is complicated by a love quadrangle and a bromance. <br/><br/>I didn&apos;t love this as much as the earlier books in the series, but it&apos;s still a pretty good read. I&apos;d have given it 4.5 stars, but I knew who the murderer was as soon as the murderer knew it.</span>
  <span id="freeText2121456050039201663" style="display:none">When Sheriff Prescote is taken captive in battle, his deputy, Hugh Beringar, seeks to exchange a young Welsh prisoner for him. The deal is made, and the injured sheriff is brought home, only to fall prey to murder. The resolution is complicated by a love quadrangle and a bromance. <br /><br />I didn't love this as much as the earlier books in the series, but it's still a pretty good read. I'd have given it 4.5 stars, but I knew who the murderer was as soon as the murderer knew it.</span>
